<DocsLayout title="API Reference">
  <h1>API Reference</h1>
  <p>
    EncodeSwarmr provides a REST API at <code>/api/v1</code> with an OpenAPI 3.1 specification available at <code>/api/v1/openapi.json</code>. The API uses JSON request/response bodies and follows RFC 9457 (Problem Details) for error responses.
  </p>

  <h2>Authentication</h2>
  <p>The API supports three authentication methods:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Session cookie</strong> — Set after login via the web UI</li>
    <li><strong>API key</strong> — Passed via <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;api-key&gt;</code> header</li>
    <li><strong>OIDC token</strong> — JWT from your identity provider</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Core Endpoints</h2>

  <h3>Sources</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>GET</code></td><td><code>/api/v1/sources</code></td><td>List all registered sources</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>POST</code></td><td><code>/api/v1/sources</code></td><td>Register a new source</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>GET</code></td><td><code>/api/v1/sources/&#123;id&#125;</code></td><td>Get source details</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>DELETE</code></td><td><code>/api/v1/sources/&#123;id&#125;</code></td><td>Remove a source</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

