  <h2>Pagination</h2>
  <p>
    List endpoints use cursor-based pagination to avoid OFFSET drift on large datasets:
  </p>
  <pre><code>GET /api/v1/jobs?limit=50&cursor=eyJpZCI6MTAwfQ==</code></pre>
  <p>
    Responses include a <code>next_cursor</code> field. Pass it as the <code>cursor</code> query parameter to fetch the next page.
  </p>

  <h2>Error Format</h2>
  <p>Errors follow RFC 9457 (Problem Details for HTTP APIs):</p>
  <pre><code>&#123;
  "type": "https://encodeswarmr.dev/errors/not-found",
  "title": "Resource Not Found",
  "status": 404,
  "detail": "Job with ID 'abc123' was not found",
  "instance": "/api/v1/jobs/abc123"
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Rate Limiting</h2>
  <p>
    The API enforces rate limits of 200 requests/second per IP with a burst allowance of 400. Rate limit headers are included in responses:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>X-RateLimit-Limit</code> — Maximum requests per second</li>
    <li><code>X-RateLimit-Remaining</code> — Remaining requests in the window</li>
    <li><code>X-RateLimit-Reset</code> — Unix timestamp when the limit resets</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>WebSocket Events</h2>
  <p>
    Connect to <code>/api/v1/ws</code> for real-time updates. Events include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>job.progress</code> — Encoding progress updates (percentage, fps, ETA)</li>
    <li><code>job.completed</code> / <code>job.failed</code> — Job state changes</li>
    <li><code>agent.online</code> / <code>agent.offline</code> — Agent connectivity changes</li>
    <li><code>agent.heartbeat</code> — Periodic agent status updates</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Generated Clients</h2>
  <p>
    Auto-generated TypeScript and Go clients are available in the <code>api/generated/</code> directory of the repository. Use <code>oapi-codegen</code> to regenerate:
  </p>
  <pre><code>make generate-api</code></pre>

